I've tried several different types of ammo, different mags, nothing helped. title: For Sale:  Daniel Defense DDM4V1LW AR-15 NIB
postcontent:
This rifle is brand new (arrived mid-February) and has only been taken out of the case in which it arrived to be examined and photographed! I was lucky enough to get an order in at Daniel Defense for some rifles before Christmas, so I ordered enough for my family. As it turns out, my brother would rather spend his money on other things (food, gas, clothing, etc.)—his loss is your gain! I don’t really want to sell this rifle, but I now own three different Daniel Defense rifles, and I don’t need this one. I hope that you’ll buy it, but, to be honest, I kinda also hope that you won’t...

Long story short, if you want an incredible rifle, this is a great one. I might choose a LaRue, Noveske, KAC or Wilson over this one (which is sad that I may never get one of these now, at least not without selling my house), but this rifle is pretty close to those super-premium rifles. I know that, from what I have seen, I wouldn’t choose any other options over this rifle (it is measurably better rifle than my Colt AR-15, which most folks consider the standard by which others are measured). If you just want to go out and do some target shooting, this will certainly work, but—to be honest—there are a lot of rifles that can do that job for significantly less. If, however, you are looking for a rifle on which you might need to bet your life, this is one on which you would feel comfortable making that bet. Go to YouTube and watch the Daniel Defense torture test and judge for yourself!

OK, so here are the vital statistics for this rifle:

MATERIALS & CONSTRUCTION

•	Magazine: MAGPUL 30 round PMag in Black
•	Vertical Grip: Daniel Defense A2 Styling Vertical Grip
•	Case: Comes with Custom Daniel Defense Full-Latch Impact Plastic Case

There will be other details, but here are some that are non-negotiable:
